itative interpretational frameworks for doing magic. Arguing with Angels offers a novel, nuanced approach to questions about how ritual magic has survived the advent of modernity and demonstrates the ways in which modern culture has recreated magical discourse.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEnochian magicxHistory. 0aOccultismxHistory. 4aArea Studies : British Studies. 4aHistory : History. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Esotericism and Gnosticism. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aRELIGION / Agnosticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438441924423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438441924/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles